  "steps": [
    "Golden Gate assembly: If the wild-type insert is obtained from PCR amplification, ensure the PCR product is cleaned. %s %s",
    "Made additional digestion mix. %s %s",
    "Aliquot 5 µL of digestion mix to each of the golden gate reactions.",
    "Set the thermal cycler for the program below: %s %s",
    "A negative control reaction with H2O instead of insert is recommended.",
    "Set the thermal cycler for the program below: %s %s SapI enzyme is less thermostable. Consider adding 1 µL of SapI enzyme after 2 hours.",
    "Purify each reaction with Zymo Clean &amp; Concentrate -5 kit.",
    "Transformation: Add 1 µL - 2 µL of DNA from sample reaction and negative control to chemical competent E. coli cells by following NEB stable competent cell transformation protocol. Quick transformation without an outgrowth period is adequate. It will reduce transformation efficiency.",
    "Incubate overnight at 30 °C for 24:00:00 .",
    "Consider to add Puc 19 and H 2 O as controls to the transformation process.",
    "Colony selection and mini prep: Check negative control plate to ensure the background colony is less than 10% of the colony counts from the sample plate.",
    "Pick 2-3 colonies for an overnight growth in 3 mL of LB + amp (1:1000) per colony for mini prep.",
    "Sequence confirmation by nanopore sequencing."
  ],
